      <hedline>
        <hl1>Will Faith Be an Issue for Voters?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Hillel Stavis letter says many Jews are less conflicted than David Margolick about Sen Joseph Lieberman's clarity of identity and Jewish faith (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>David Margolick (Op-Ed, Aug. 12) does a disservice to his fellow Jews who may not be as assimilated as he is. While Mr. Margolick may ''squirm'' at Senator Joseph I. Lieberman's ''conspicuous religiosity,'' many other Jews are less conflicted about the senator's clarity of identity and faith.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>David Margolick (Op-Ed, Aug. 12) does a disservice to his fellow Jews who may not be as assimilated as he is. While Mr. Margolick may ''squirm'' at Senator Joseph I. Lieberman's ''conspicuous religiosity,'' many other Jews are less conflicted about the senator's clarity of identity and faith.</p>
        <p>One wonders if Mr. Margolick was similarly discomfited by the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.'s or the Rev. Jesse Jackson's ''conspicuous religiosity.''</p>
        <p>HILLEL STAVIS  Freedom, N.H., Aug. 12, 200</p>
      </block>
